.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-storage - Manage on-node S3-compatible object storage


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel storage [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run an S3-compatible object store on this node, backed by VersityGW.

.PP
Objects are stored under ~/.citadel/storage/data and survive restarts. The
gateway is published on 127.0.0.1 only (never 0.0.0.0). Root credentials are
minted once on first start and reused on every restart, so stored objects and
presigned URLs remain valid.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for storage


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-storage-start(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-storage-status(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-storage-stop(1)\fP
